-- Bank stocks, earnings push Hong Kong index up 0.7 pct
-- By Alice Woodhouse
-- Wed Mar 26, 2014 04:07AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, March 26 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares closed at a two-week high on Wednesday, buoyed by financial counters and strong gains from dairy giant China Mengniu on its earnings results.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> ended up 0.7 percent at 21,887.75, its highest close since March 12. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the top Chinese listings in Hong Kong closed up 1.6 percent. Shares in Agricultural Bank of China <1288.HK> rose 3.4 percent as investors took comfort in its declining level of  non-performing loans (NPLs) and an increase in net interest margins. [ID:nL4N0MM27F]